  "text": "Among many other physico-chemical parameters, a very good relationship between Giardia cyst occurrence and raw water quality parameters was found in Canadian province by LeChevallier et al. (1991) . The pH level of the water was kept for avoiding corrosion in the water reutilization system. The turbidity values contributed to assuring the removal of Giardia cysts [CITATION_1] ). There was a positive correlation between TDS and the number of Giardia cysts found. The positive correlation between conductivity and the number of Giardia cysts in the wastewater effulents; and negative correlation with temperature in the present study was significant at 0.05 level. TDS and conductivity values Log (Number of Giardia + 1) indicate the presence of organic and inorganic nutrients for the organisms which might help Giardia cysts to servive.",
